explanation: The solution uses a stack to track the opening parentheses and count the number of moves required to make the string valid. It iterates through the string, pushing opening parentheses onto the stack and popping them when a closing parenthesis is encountered. If a closing parenthesis is encountered when the stack is empty, it increments the count. The final count is the sum of the remaining opening parentheses in the stack and the count of closing parentheses without matching opening parentheses.

